The paper discusses the consensus mechanism, membership selection, and structure of blockchains, which are all related to computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes an evaluation framework for analyzing blockchain systems, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the properties achieved by different blockchain systems, which can be considered as a system analysis and control (cs.SY) topic.
